snippet: Overseeing the business of medicine is big business.
abstract: News analysis; analysis of base pay of insurance executives, hospital executives and even hospital administrators shows that they are often paid more than doctors; proliferation of high earners in the medical business and administration ranks adds to United States' $3.7 trillion health care bill and stands in stark contrast with other developed countries.
lead_paragraph: Overseeing the business of medicine is big business.

headline.main: Medicine’s Top Earners Are Not the M.D.s
headline.print_headline: Doctor’s Salaries Are Not the Big Cost
